adjective.description: Having or involving several parts, elements, or members.

noun.description: A number that can be divided by another number without a remainder.
examples: 15, 20, or any other multiple of five

noun.description: An arrangement of terminals that allows connection with an electrical circuit at any one of several points.

origin: Mid 17th century: from French, from late Latin multiplus, alteration of Latin multiplex (see multiplex).
